  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Unrepentance of Israel and Judah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come, let us return to the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For He has torn us to pieces,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He will heal us;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has wounded us,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He will bind up our wounds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "After two days He will revive us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the third day He will raise us up,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that we may live in His presence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So let us knowâ€”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us press on to know the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "As surely as the sun rises,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will appear;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will come to us like the rain,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the spring showers that water the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What shall I do with you, O Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2475
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What shall I do with you, O Judah?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For your loyalty is like a morning mist,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the early dew that vanishes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I have hewn them by the prophets;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have slain them by the words of My mouth,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and My judgments go forth like lightning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I desire mercy, not sacrifice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2476
          },
          {
            "text": "and the knowledge of God",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "rather than burnt offerings.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But they, like Adam, have transgressed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2477
          },
          {
            "text": "the covenant;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there they were unfaithful to Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Gilead is a city of evildoers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "tracked with footprints of blood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like raiders who lie in ambush,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so does a band of priests;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they murder on the way to Shechem;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "surely they have committed atrocities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the house of Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have seen a horrible thing:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ephraim practices prostitution there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel is defiled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Also for you, O Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a harvest is appointed,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when I restore",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My people from captivity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2478
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2475,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verse 10",
        "reference": {
